#: ../../../source/docs/tools_reference/emsdk.rst:5
msgid "Emscripten SDK (emsdk)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../source/docs/tools_reference/emsdk.rst:7
msgid ""
"**Emscripten SDK (** ``emsdk`` **) is used to perform all SDK maintenance. "
"You only need to install the SDK once; after that emsdk can do all further "
"updates!**"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../source/docs/tools_reference/emsdk.rst:9
msgid ""
"With *emsdk* you can download, install or remove *any* :term:`SDK` or :term:"
"`Tool`, and even use the :ref:`bleeding edge versions <emsdk-dev-sdk>` in "
"development on GitHub. To access the *emsdk* on Windows, first launch the :"
"ref:`Emscripten Command Prompt <emcmdprompt>`. Most operations are of the "
"form ``./emsdk command``."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../source/docs/tools_reference/emsdk.rst:11
msgid ""
"This document provides the command syntax, and a :ref:`set of guides "
"<emsdk_howto>` explaining how to perform both common and advanced "
"maintenance operations."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../source/docs/tools_reference/emsdk.rst:14
msgid "Command line syntax"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../source/docs/tools_reference/emsdk.rst:16
msgid ""
"**./emsdk** [**help** | **list** [**--old**] | **update** | **install** "
"*<tool/sdk>* | **uninstall** *<tool/sdk>* | **activate** *<tool/sdk>*]"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../source/docs/tools_reference/emsdk.rst:20
msgid "Arguments"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../source/docs/tools_reference/emsdk.rst:28
msgid "Command"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../source/docs/tools_reference/emsdk.rst:29
msgid "Description"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../source/docs/tools_reference/emsdk.rst:30
msgid "``list [--old]``"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../source/docs/tools_reference/emsdk.rst:31
msgid ""
"Lists all current SDKs and tools and their installation status. With the ``--"
"old`` parameter, historical versions are also shown."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../source/docs/tools_reference/emsdk.rst:32
msgid "``update``"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../source/docs/tools_reference/emsdk.rst:33
msgid ""
"Fetches the latest list of all available tools and SDKs (but does not "
"install them)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../source/docs/tools_reference/emsdk.rst:34
msgid "``install <tool/sdk>``"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../source/docs/tools_reference/emsdk.rst:35
msgid ""
"Downloads and installs the :ref:`specified tool or SDK <emsdk-specified-tool-"
"sdk>`."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../source/docs/tools_reference/emsdk.rst:36
msgid "``uninstall <tool/sdk>``"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../source/docs/tools_reference/emsdk.rst:37
msgid ""
"Removes the :ref:`specified tool or SDK <emsdk-specified-tool-sdk>` from the "
"disk."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../source/docs/tools_reference/emsdk.rst:38
msgid "``activate <tool/sdk>``"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../source/docs/tools_reference/emsdk.rst:39
msgid ""
"Sets the :ref:`specified tool or SDK <emsdk-specified-tool-sdk>` as the "
"default tool in the system environment. On Linux you additionally have to "
"enable the environment settings using ``source ./emsdk_env.sh``, as "
"described in \":ref:`emsdk-set-active-tools`\"."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../source/docs/tools_reference/emsdk.rst:40
msgid "``help``"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../source/docs/tools_reference/emsdk.rst:41
msgid ""
"Lists all supported commands. The same list is output if no command is "
"specified."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../source/docs/tools_reference/emsdk.rst:45
msgid ""
"For Linux and macOS the commands are called with **./emsdk**. On Windows use "
"**emsdk**."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../source/docs/tools_reference/emsdk.rst:50
msgid "Tools and SDK targets"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../source/docs/tools_reference/emsdk.rst:52
msgid ""
"The ``<tool/sdk>`` given above as a command argument is one of the targets "
"listed using ``./emsdk list`` (or ``./emsdk list --old``)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../source/docs/tools_reference/emsdk.rst:54
msgid ""
"Note that some of the tools and SDK names include  *master* or *main*: these "
"targets are used to clone and pull the very latest versions from the "
"Emscripten main and master branches."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../source/docs/tools_reference/emsdk.rst:56
msgid ""
"You can also specify a target of ``latest`` to grab the most current SDK."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../source/docs/tools_reference/emsdk.rst:61
msgid "SDK concepts"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../source/docs/tools_reference/emsdk.rst:63
msgid ""
"The Emscripten toolchain includes a number of different tools, including "
"*Clang*, *Emscripten*, *Java*, *Git*, *Node*, etc. *Emsdk* is a small "
"package manager for controlling which tools are installed, and from the set "
"of installed tools, which are active."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../source/docs/tools_reference/emsdk.rst:65
msgid ""
"The current set of available :term:`tools <Tool>` and :term:`SDKs <SDK>` are "
"listed using ``./emsdk list``. These can be installed individually (``./"
"emsdk install node-0.10.17-64bit``) or as a group (``./emsdk install "
"node-0.10.17-64bit java-7.45-64bit``)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../source/docs/tools_reference/emsdk.rst:67
msgid ""
"The :term:`SDK` targets are a convenience mechanism for specifying the full "
"set of tools used by a particular Emscripten release. For example, the two "
"lines below are equivalent: ::"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../source/docs/tools_reference/emsdk.rst:72
msgid ""
"A particular installed SDK (or tool) can then be set as :term:`active "
"<Active Tool/SDK>`, meaning that it will be used when Emscripten is run. The "
"active \"compiler configuration\" is stored is a config file (*.emscripten*) "
"within the emsdk directory."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../source/docs/tools_reference/emsdk.rst:77
msgid ""
"The different tools and SDKs managed by *emsdk* are stored in different "
"directories under the root folder you specified when you first installed an "
"SDK, grouped by tool and version."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../source/docs/tools_reference/emsdk.rst:83
msgid "Emscripten Compiler Configuration File (.emscripten)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../source/docs/tools_reference/emsdk.rst:85
msgid ""
"The *Compiler Configuration File* stores the :term:`active <Active Tool/"
"SDK>` configuration on behalf of the *emsdk*. The active configuration "
"defines the specific set of tools that are used by default if Emscripten in "
"called on the :ref:`Emscripten Command Prompt <emcmdprompt>`."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../source/docs/tools_reference/emsdk.rst:87
msgid ""
"The configuration file is named **.emscripten**. It is emsdk-specific, so it "
"won't conflict with any config file the user might have elsewhere on their "
"system."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../source/docs/tools_reference/emsdk.rst:91
msgid ""
"The file should generally not be updated directly unless you're :ref:"
"`building Emscripten from source <installing-from-source>`. Instead, use the "
"*emsdk* to activate specific SDKs and tools as needed (``emsdk activate "
"<tool/SDK>``)."
msgstr ""

